      <p>Modern CSS frameworks like Pico CSS offer several advantages:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Your markup stays clean and meaningful</li>
        <li><strong>Modular architecture:</strong> Organized into maintainable partials</li>
        <li><strong>Comprehensive theming:</strong> Dark/light modes with design tokens</li>
        <li><strong>Progressive enhancement:</strong> Styles work even with CSS disabled</li>
        <li><strong>Developer experience:</strong> Easy to customize and extend</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This modular approach aligns perfectly with the Progressive Islands architecture, where we prioritize maintainability and scalability.</p>
